ANC branches from Limpopo have gathered at Luthuli House to demand the reinstatement of two leaders, implicated in the VBS report. Courtesy of #DSTV403 PRETORIA - ANC branches from Limpopo gathered at Luthuli House to demand resolution for two leaders, implicated in the VBS report on Monday. The branches demanded that the ANC either reinstate them or begin the process of disciplinary hearings. READ: PIC welcomes decision to declare two former VBS directors delinquent The branches dispersed in the afternoon after asking that former-Limpopo ANC deputy chairperson Florence Radzilani and former-Limpopo ANC treasurer Danny Msiza be reinstated or disciplined. READ: Maile cautions ANC members to stop speaking as free agents The protestors asked that the former leaders be immediately reinstated or partake in an internal disciplinary process. ANC secretary-general Ace Magashule addressed the picketers and promised the party would set up a committee to resolve the issue.